parameters.name: name
parameters.description: object name

parameters.name: refers_to
parameters.description: Filter to request all objects that refers to another Avi resource. Its syntax is refers_to=<obj_type>:<obj_uuid>. Eg. get all virtual services referring to pool p1 will be refers_to=pool:pool_p1_uuid

parameters.name: referred_by
parameters.description: Filter to request all objects that are referred by another Avi resource. Its syntax is referred_by=<obj_type>:<obj_uuid>. Eg. get all pools referred_by virtual service vs1 - referred_by=virtualservice:vs_vs1_uuid

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: List of fields to be returned for the resource. Some fields like name, URL, uuid etc. are always returned.

parameters.name: include_name
parameters.description: All the Avi REST reference URIs have a name suffix as URI#name. It is useful to get the referenced resource name without performing get on that object.

parameters.name: skip_default
parameters.description: Default values are not set.

parameters.name: join_subresources
parameters.description: It automatically returns additional dependent resources like runtime. Eg. join_subresources=runtime.

parameters.name: X-Avi-Tenant
parameters.description: Avi Tenant Header

parameters.name: X-Avi-Tenant-UUID
parameters.description: Avi Tenant Header UUID

parameters.name: X-Avi-Version
parameters.description: The caller is required to set Avi Version Header to the expected version of configuration. The response from the controller will provide and accept data according to the specified version. The controller will reject POST and PUT requests where the data is not compatible with the specified version.

parameters.name: X-CSRFToken
parameters.description: Avi Controller may send back CSRF token in the response cookies. The caller should update the request headers with this token else controller will reject requests.

version.description: Protobuf version number. Gets incremented if there is se Diff of federated diff in config pbs.This field will be a monotonically increasing number indicating the number of Config Update operations. Field introduced in 21.1.1. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials edition with any value, Basic edition with any value, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

addr.description: IP address. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

type.description: Enum options - V4, DNS, V6. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

addrs.description: IP address(es). Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

group_refs.description: UUID of IP address group(s). It is a reference to an object of type IpAddrGroup. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

match_criteria.description: Criterion to use for IP address matching the HTTP request. Enum options - IS_IN, IS_NOT_IN. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

prefixes.description: IP address prefix(es). Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

ranges.description: IP address range(s). Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

ip_addr.description: Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

mask.description: Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

begin.description: Starting IP address of the range. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

end.description: Ending IP address of the range. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

key.description: Key. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

value.description: Value. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

match_criteria.description: Criterion to use for transport protocol matching. Enum options - IS_IN, IS_NOT_IN. Field introduced in 17.2.7. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

protocol.description: Transport protocol to match. Enum options - PROTOCOL_ICMP, PROTOCOL_TCP, PROTOCOL_UDP, PROTOCOL_SCTP. Field introduced in 17.2.7. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

nat_ip.description: Nat IP address. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

nat_ip_range.description: Nat IP address range. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

destination_ip.description: Destination IP of the packet. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

services.description: Services like port-matching and protocol. Field introduced in 18.2.5. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

source_ip.description: Source IP of the packet. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

_last_modified.description: UNIX time since epoch in microseconds. Units(MICROSECONDS).

configpb_attributes.description: Protobuf versioning for config pbs. Field introduced in 21.1.1. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials edition with any value, Basic edition with any value, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

created_by.description: Creator name. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

description.description: Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

markers.description: List of labels to be used for granular RBAC. Field introduced in 20.1.5. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials edition with any value, Basic edition with any value, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

name.description: Name of the Nat policy. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

rules.description: Nat policy Rules. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

tenant_ref.description: It is a reference to an object of type Tenant. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

uuid.description: UUID of the Nat policy. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

nat_info.description: Pool of IP Addresses used for Nat. Field introduced in 18.2.5. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

type.description: Nat Action Type. Enum options - NAT_POLICY_ACTION_TYPE_DYNAMIC_IP_PORT. Field introduced in 18.2.5. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

action.description: Nat rule Action Information. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

created_by.description: Creator name. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

enable.description: Nat rule enable flag. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

index.description: Nat rule Index. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

match.description: Nat rule Match Criteria. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

name.description: Nat rule Name. Field introduced in 18.2.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

match_criteria.description: Criterion to use for port matching the HTTP request. Enum options - IS_IN, IS_NOT_IN. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

ports.description: Listening TCP port(s). Allowed values are 1-65535. Minimum of 1 items required. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

key.description: Key for filter match. Field introduced in 20.1.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

values.description: Values for filter match. Multiple values will be evaluated as OR. Example  key = value1 OR key = value2. Behavior for match is key = * if this field is empty. Field introduced in 20.1.3. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

destination_port.description: Destination Port of the packet. Field introduced in 18.2.5. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

protocol.description: Protocol to match. Supported protocols are TCP, UDP and ICMP. Field introduced in 20.1.1. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.

source_port.description: Source Port of the packet. Field introduced in 18.2.5. Allowed in Enterprise edition with any value, Essentials, Basic, Enterprise with Cloud Services edition.
